main event: An unidentified object the size of a dime was observed at arm's length, appearing in the ESE at a 50-degree elevation and then fading away.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for thirty-five minutes., The object was stationary during the observation., The object was reported to probably be an astronomical star., No bright star was found in the Air Almanac for the exact spot., The report includes comments from the reporting officer suggesting it's likely a star.
sighted object: unknown object, size of a dime
witness description: the reporting officer believed the object was likely a star
